('css','CSS HOME','css-home','Entry point for CSS learning journey.','CSS is essential for styling websites and making them look good.','CSS allows you to add colors, fonts, spacing, and layout to HTML elements.','CSS adds style to HTML. It uses selectors and properties. Supports responsive design.','beginner',1,false),
('css','CSS Introduction','css-introduction','What CSS is and how it works.','Understanding CSS basics is the first step to becoming a front-end developer.','CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It attaches style rules to HTML elements.','Selector {property:value;} syntax. Cascading and inheritance.','beginner',2,false),
('css','CSS Syntax','css-syntax','Learn CSS rule syntax and structure.','Proper syntax prevents errors and makes styles effective.','CSS rules are made of selectors, braces, properties, and values. Multiple rules cascade.','selector, property, value, declaration block, comments.','beginner',3,false),
('css','CSS Selectors','css-selectors','Pick elements to style with selectors.','Selectors are the most powerful part of CSS, controlling which elements get styles.','Types: element, class, id, attribute, pseudo-class, pseudo-element.','element, .class, #id, *, combinators, pseudo-classes.','beginner',4,false),
('css','CSS How To','css-how-to','Practical usage examples and quick tasks.','Guides for common CSS tasks speed up learning and development.','How to center elements, create responsive layouts, style forms, etc.','copy/paste patterns for daily needs.','beginner',5,false),
('css','CSS Comments','css-comments','Write comments in CSS.','Comments document style rules and make them easier to maintain.','Use /* comment */ in CSS; ignored by browser.','Multi-line comments; no nesting.','beginner',6,false),
